# Integration Testing Standard

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/testing/integration.md](../../docs/agent/standards/testing/integration.md)

- Integration tests run against real Postgres + Redis via Docker Compose. **Do not mock Prisma.**
- Truncate all tables in `beforeEach` — use `prisma.$executeRaw` or a helper that truncates in FK-safe order.
- Use a dedicated `TEST_DATABASE_URL` pointing to the Docker Compose Postgres DB.
- No live HTTP calls to external services (use `nock` or environment flags to disable outbound requests).
- Test file naming: `{domain}.integration.spec.ts` in `test/integration/`.
- Each test file sets up its own `NestJS TestingModule` with real providers (no mocks for DB/Redis).
- Redis: flush with `redis.flushdb()` in `beforeEach`.
- MinIO: use the Docker Compose MinIO instance with a dedicated test bucket.
